                          <p class="Para">Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) gains increasing importance as a new, flexible provisioning model for IT resources. However, its uptake in the enterprise environment is not without its challenges; among the most important ones are organizational issues. This paper presents an IaaS acceptance model based on multiple theoretical dimensions , which focuses on organizational drivers and barriers to IaaS deployment. It was challenged in a series of expert interviews and the resulting hypotheses give new insights into IaaS adoption drivers and represent a solid foundation for future empirical studies.</p>
